'''Giuseppe Vigoni''' (9 July 1846 – 15 February 1914) was an [[Italians|Italian]] explorer of [[Africa]] and geographer. He was a recipient of the [[Order of Saints Maurice and Lazarus]]. He was mayor of [[Milan]]. He served in the Senate of the [[Kingdom of Italy]].

