{{other uses|Helderberg (disambiguation)}}
{{Infobox South African town 2011 | name = Helderberg | native_name = | other_name = | image_skyline = Helderberg mountain seen from the North-West 9669.jpg | image_caption = [[Helderberg Mountain]] seen more or less from the South-West | coordinates = {{coord|34|5|00|S|18|55|00|E|region:ZA|display=inline,title}} | province = Western Cape | district = | municipality = City of Cape Town | established_date = | government_type = <!-- Ward 00 --> | leader_party = | leader_title = Councillor | leader_name = | area_footnotes = | area_total_km2 = | elevation_m = | population_footnotes = | population_total = | population_as_of = | postal_code = | postal2_code = | area_code = | censuscode = | website = }}
'''Helderberg''' is a wine-producing area in the [[Western Cape]] of [[South Africa]] and an area of [[Cape Town]]
Originally known as the "[[Hottentots-Holland]]" area, it was renamed "Helderberg" by the [[City of Cape Town]] following concerns about possible [[racist]] [[connotation]]s in the name. However, many people who live there still refer to it by its former name.
The Helderberg consists of [[Somerset West]], [[Strand, Western Cape|Strand]], [[Gordons Bay]] and a few other towns. The district takes its name from the imposing [[Helderberg Mountain]], which is [[Afrikaans]] for "bright mountain", referring to the way in which the Western side of the mountain is illuminated in the evenings, and culminates at a height of 1137m as The Dome.
Local media in the region include the ''District Mail'', a local newspaper, and ''[[Radio Helderberg]]''.
