{{Infobox book| <!-- See [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Novels]] or [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Books]] --> | name =The Wild North | title_orig = | translator = | image = | caption = | author = [[Ion Idriess]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = Australia | language = English | series = | genre = short story collection | publisher = [[Angus and Robertson]] | release_date = 1960 | english_release_date = | media_type = | pages = 229 | isbn = | preceded_by = | followed_by = }} '''''The Wild North''''' is a 1960 book by [[Ion Idriess]]. It is a collection of 24 short stories and sketches about [[Cape York Peninsula|Cape York]], some of which were written early in Idriess' career.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article103111455 |title=PEN THAT NEVER RUNS DRY |newspaper=[[The Canberra Times]] |volume=35, |issue=9,775 |location=Australian Capital Territory, Australia |date=3 December 1960 |accessdate=16 April 2016 |page=15 |via=National Library of Australia}} </ref>
